This paper deals with the problem of patrolling a line segment using mobile agents, which is a topic in multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and strategies for the problem, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper includes geometric arguments and considerations, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
